  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals are often required to report suspicious activities to designated authorities. Specific requirements can vary by jurisdiction, but generally include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n2. Know Your Customer (KYC) compliance\n3. Transaction monitoring\n4. Record-keeping requirements\n5. Potential penalties for non-reporting\n\nConsulting local legal guidelines is recommended for specific details.",
